sampleEvents.name: Representing India:  at CHPS International Education Week
sampleEvents.description: Represented India at CHPS International Education Week by highlighting Indian culture and promoting healthy living. Provided health-conscious Indian foods while educating attendees on the connection between nutrition and cancer prevention through the Cancer Shield Club. Our table focused on celebrating culture, fostering global connections, and raising awareness about preventative health practices.

sampleEvents.name: Sunday Worship at Faith UMC with Wesley
sampleEvents.description: Join us at Faith United Methodist Church every Sunday for worship starting at 10:00 a.m.    Faith UMC shares our mission to alleviate poverty, and we are so excited to partner with their community. Rev. Erwin Lopez will serve as pastor and preach every Sunday.    A bus will leave from the Wesley Foundation on UCF Campus at 9:15 a.m. to transport those needed to Faith UMC. Immediately following the service, a free brunch will be provided! Hope to see you there!

sampleOrganizations.name: American Society of Highway Engineers
sampleOrganizations.description: Our Mission To provide a forum for UCF student members interested in the highway industry that supports education, innovation, and fellowship; promoting a safe and efficient highway system for mobility now and in the future.

sampleOrganizations.name: Next Gen Engineering
sampleOrganizations.description: Next Gen Engineering is a student led organization focused investigating innovative solutions to real world problems. NGE uses multidisciplinary projects as a means to promote collaborative problem solving, and to provide an industry like an environment experience to our members. NGE is also a big supporter of collaborative projects and events between RSOs! So regardless of if you are a student or an organization, we would like to connect with you and hope to build a brighter more innovative tomorrow!

sampleOrganizations.name: Surf Club and Team @ UCF
sampleOrganizations.description: The Surf Club & Team at UCF is a student run organization that provides a place for surfers and non-surfers alike to meet and enjoy the beach together. The Surf Club is one of the largest non-greek organizations on campus with around 100 members each year. We host lots of events, such as beach cleanups, alumni contests, tailgates, beach days, and movie nights. Our club is a great way to make friends and catch rides to the beach! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T7YHtTO7EeI
